Dormole Limited is a privately owned company incorporated in 1974.

The Company has grown through the development of a number of subsidiary companies which primarily specialise in the development and distribution of tools and associated products. 

The core philosophy of the Company is to work closely with our customers, suppliers and staff to develop the business.

Dormole continues  to re-invest in the business to ensure that we can provide the best possible levels of service and support to our customers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/78c52f2a-e9ad-47ed-b319-149c6ea4e6d5.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-03-04T00:00:00+00:00', '78c52f2a-e9ad-47ed-b319-149c6ea4e6d5') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Dévorer', 'DEVORER LTD', 'https://devorer.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/d%c3%a9vorer', 'Dévorer (DEVORER LTD) is a UK-based, student-led company founded in 2022 that creates a data-powered campus dining ecosystem. It partners with over 300 premium street food vendors to provide affordable and diverse global cuisines to university students and staff. The company operates a flexible dining solution that enhances existing campus catering without competition, utilizing autonomous systems for efficient service.

Dévorer emphasizes sustainability and aims to reduce food waste by involving students in its operations and initiatives. It offers over 40 rotating global cuisines, including halal and vegan options, and subsidizes meal prices through vendor partnerships. The company employs AI and computer vision to analyze student behavior, optimize vendor selection, and personalize offerings. Additionally, it operates an automated pop-up marketplace for brand activations, including custom-branded food trucks that tour campuses, engaging students through unique dining experiences.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/11effe8c-d98b-4a61-97a2-132611088bc8.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-02-25T00:00:00+00:00', '11effe8c-d98b-4a61-97a2-132611088bc8') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Egis', 'EGIS UK - CONSULTING AND ENGINEERING LIMITED', 'https://www.egis-group.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/egis', 'Egis is a global engineering, architecture, consulting, construction, and operations firm based in Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines, France. Founded in 1947, the company specializes in sustainable infrastructure, mobility services, and digital transformation across various sectors, including transport, urban development, energy, and the environment. With over 22,000 employees in more than 100 countries, Egis aims to address climate challenges and urbanization through innovative solutions, targeting a position among the top 10 global engineering firms and exceeding €4 billion in revenue by 2029.

Egis offers comprehensive services in engineering, consulting, construction, and operations, focusing on intelligent infrastructure and resilient territorial development. Their expertise includes digital engineering, railway and transport solutions, civil engineering, and environmental services. The firm also provides advanced technological solutions such as Digital Twins, Building Information Modelling (BIM), and AI-driven outcomes. Egis has established partnerships with major public and private entities, contributing to significant projects worldwide, including healthcare clusters in Singapore and solar power implementations in Ukraine.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 133, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/35ed5be7-54b5-4242-a2be-b12cea6b0c5b.png', TRUE, 'Very large company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-03-06T00:00:00+00:00', '35ed5be7-54b5-4242-a2be-b12cea6b0c5b') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Elecsis', 'Elecsis Limited', 'https://www.elecsis.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/elecsis-switchgear-ltd', 'Elecsis is a multi discipline engineering Services Company based in Bridgwater, Somerset where they offer design, manufacture, testing, installation and commissioning of electrical switchgear and process control equipment covering both MV and LV applications. Elecsis offer a wide range of fully type tested equipment not only to the required electrical standards of IEC 60439 and 61439 but also IEC 61641 Arc Containment incorporating both ABB and Schneider equipment, shock (up to 70g), seismic and EMC. Dealing with blue chip companies worldwide across all major sectors including the MoD their core business being MV/LV switchgear, package sub-stations, sub-distribution equipment, Motor Control Centres, process PLC cabinets for which they also develop and write the process logic code and SCADA systems for schemes where competitively priced, technically compliant, quality products are required to meet client deadlines. Elecsis also have dedicated installation teams for busbar (standard and cast resin) and cabling and offer many forms of training both on and off site. 
Elecsis are pleased to announce that after successfully working since 2013 with KTE, South Korea''s largest award winning switchgear manufacturing company on multi-million pound switchgear contracts for UK, Norwegian and Thai government projects, KTE has now acquired Elecsis as it''s UK and European facility.
KTE have a turnover of $100M, in excess of 250 personnel and have been awarded numerous government awards and manufacture a wide range of products including MV and LV switchgear for marine and industrial applications worldwide. With continual investment in their large R&D department they are at the forefront of their field and with Elecsis have jointly developed ranges of arc contained switchgear using ABB and Schneider components. 
The KTE range of equipment, including withdrawable MV has enhanced our already wide and diverse type tested product range with fault levels  up to 130kA to add to our own including which cover shock, vibration, seismic, EMC and arc containment. 
www.kte.co.kr', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/848bf059-de5a-4672-b28c-0a127379b0a4.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-18T00:00:00+00:00', '848bf059-de5a-4672-b28c-0a127379b0a4') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Ellmer Construction', 'F. B. Ellmer Limited', 'https://ellmers.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ellmer-construction', 'Ellmer is a construction company based in London, established in 1875 and a member of the Byrne Group since 1977. The company specializes in high-quality fit-out, refurbishment, and new developments across various sectors, including high-end residential, commercial property, retail, leisure, and hospitality projects.

Ellmer offers a range of services, including complex refurbishments, new build developments, and multi-trade contracting. The company is skilled in programming, design, and construction processes, providing preconstruction advice and leveraging the technical expertise of its parent company. Notable projects include the refurbishment of The Cutty Sark and hospitality suites at Twickenham Stadium. Ellmer''s client base features commercial property companies, hotel operators, and estate owners like The Crown and Grosvenor. The company values team commitment and mutual respect, fostering long-lasting relationships with clients and consultants.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1f69beec-7341-46de-ba5a-8954141c716d.png', TRUE, 'Medium-sized company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-11T00:00:00+00:00', '1f69beec-7341-46de-ba5a-8954141c716d') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Energex', 'Energex Partners Limited', 'https://energex.partners', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/energex-partners', 'Energex Partners is a strategic advisory consulting firm focused on the energy and utility sectors. Founded in 2025 by three former utility executives, the firm leverages over 75 years of combined experience to address complex energy challenges in Canada. Energex Partners specializes in policy, regulatory navigation, business strategy, and project development, primarily in electricity and natural gas markets. The firm is committed to fostering Indigenous partnerships to promote reliable energy and economic prosperity in communities.

The firm offers a range of advisory services, including strategies for utilities and municipalities on regulatory matters, business and project development support, and commercial advice for mergers and acquisitions. Energex Partners also provides expertise in energy procurement, risk management, and energy transition planning. With a strong emphasis on integrity, trust, and collaboration, the firm aims to deliver sustainable growth solutions for its clients, which include Indigenous organizations, municipalities, utilities, and various market participants.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6a69943f-655f-4206-b87f-93c2b896ada6.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-03-06T00:00:00+00:00', '6a69943f-655f-4206-b87f-93c2b896ada6') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Equias B.V.', 'Equias Ltd', 'https://www.equias.org', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/equias', 'Equias B.V. is a Dutch company based in Amsterdam, founded in 2004 and originally known as EFETnet. It specializes in post-trade automation services for the European energy trading market. With over 20 years of experience, Equias supports more than 1,500 clients by enhancing efficiency, security, and profitability in energy trading through streamlined trade settlement, confirmation, regulatory reporting, and monitoring.

The company operates the largest independent Registered Reporting Mechanism (RRM) under REMIT and provides a range of post-trade automation tools tailored for the energy sector. These include trade confirmation, settlement matching, and regulatory reporting services that facilitate the full trading lifecycle and manage risk. Equias aims to foster a dynamic community in European energy trading, making access open to all participants and enabling traders to operate confidently in the market.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/87e19e30-2eb7-42aa-b933-f84537097f5e.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-16T00:00:00+00:00', '87e19e30-2eb7-42aa-b933-f84537097f5e') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Eunice AI', 'Reasoon Limited', 'https://eunice.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/euniceai', 'Eunice is a London-based fintech company founded in 2022, specializing in AI-powered compliance and risk management solutions for the cryptocurrency sector. The company focuses on helping crypto businesses navigate regulatory challenges while maintaining operational efficiency in a rapidly changing environment.Eunice''s platform offers real-time due diligence, risk monitoring, and regulatory classification of digital assets. It features automated token classification with over 98% accuracy, continuous risk assessment tailored to the crypto market, and compliance-ready insights that convert fragmented data into actionable intelligence. Additionally, Eunice provides access to over 30 regulatory and risk templates to assist with compliance across various jurisdictions. The platform utilizes large language models and a hybrid human-in-the-loop validation model to ensure reliable and auditable outputs.In early 2025, Eunice launched the MiCA Whitepaper Library, an AI-driven tool that simplifies compliance with the EU''s Markets in Crypto Assets Regulation, allowing exchanges and crypto projects to create compliant whitepapers quickly. The company serves institutional clients, including exchanges and compliance teams within digital asset organizations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a4f309f1-6d92-4447-8d5c-2f78ac9ff484.png', TRUE, NULL, 1, NULL, FALSE, NULL, 'a4f309f1-6d92-4447-8d5c-2f78ac9ff484') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Exevion', 'Exevion Limited', 'https://www.exevion.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/exevion', 'Exevion Limited is a UK-based management consultancy firm founded on March 23, 2021. The company specializes in cost optimization, process improvement, efficiency realization, and digital transformation, primarily serving the Financial Services, Retail & Consumer, and Mergers & Acquisitions sectors. Exevion aims to make consultancy services accessible to businesses of all sizes, from global brands to startups, through a team of experienced consultants and independent associates.

The firm focuses on delivering measurable results with a cost-effective approach. Its core services include shaping strategic business objectives, managing change programs, and improving operational efficiency. Exevion also has a dedicated digital arm that offers bespoke solutions in digital strategy, data analytics, and project management. The leadership team includes experienced professionals with expertise in various industries, including eCommerce and payments. Exevion has worked with notable clients such as Sky, Worldpay, and Concardis, providing support for product launches and digital transformations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5d0b1cee-5acb-4add-824e-b208e192f83e.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-03-05T00:00:00+00:00', '5d0b1cee-5acb-4add-824e-b208e192f83e') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Explain Market Research', 'Explain Market Research Ltd', 'https://www.explainresearch.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/www.explainresearch.co.uk', 'Explain Market Research Limited is a UK-based full-service market research agency that specializes in bespoke qualitative, quantitative, and digital research methodologies. Founded in 1993, the company is dedicated to delivering strategic insights for organizations throughout the UK. It operates in the market research and public opinion polling sector, providing tailored research projects to help clients gain clarity and solve problems.

The agency emphasizes its commitment to in-house bespoke solutions, ensuring that clients receive personalized services rather than off-the-shelf options. With an estimated revenue between $10 to 50 million, Explain Market Research Limited has established a strong presence in the competitive market research industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/02d4701a-c1db-4458-94c4-21f905d13fbd.png', TRUE, 'Medium-sized company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-02-23T00:00:00+00:00', '02d4701a-c1db-4458-94c4-21f905d13fbd') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('FP McCann', 'FP McCann Ltd', 'https://fpmccann.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fp-mccann', 'FP McCann Ltd is the largest manufacturer and supplier of precast concrete solutions in the United Kingdom. This family-run business operates 13-14 ISO9001-accredited manufacturing facilities across the UK and Northern Ireland, employing around 1,600-1,700 people. Headquartered in Magherafelt, Northern Ireland, FP McCann has expanded through a strategic acquisition program and engages in construction projects from conception to completion.

The company offers a wide range of high-quality precast concrete products, including drainage solutions, tunnels, rail and infrastructure products, walling, flooring systems, and bespoke precast solutions. In addition to manufacturing, FP McCann provides construction management services, ensuring projects are tailored to meet client specifications. The company is committed to quality, sustainability, and innovation, addressing the needs of the building and civil engineering sectors across the UK and Ireland.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6ceed136-4218-49f0-8325-46c2bfbb382d.png', TRUE, 'Very large company', 69, NULL, FALSE, '2026-03-06T00:00:00+00:00', '6ceed136-4218-49f0-8325-46c2bfbb382d') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Farago Projects', 'Farago Projects LTD', 'https://www.farago-projects.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/farago-projects-ltd', 'Farago Projects LTD is a creative production company based in London and Paris, offering full-scale production services globally. Established in 2012, the company specializes in media production, broadcasting, and internet sectors, focusing on stills, videos, and various creative projects.

The company provides a range of services, including video and film production, still photography, motion graphics, post-production, and commercial production. Farago Projects also engages in marketing production, branding projects, and content creation for multimedia platforms. As of August 2024, Farago Projects reported a turnover of £12.46 million and employs around 12 people.

Farago Projects has collaborated with notable publications like W Magazine and Modern Weekly Style Magazine, and has worked with prominent figures in the industry. The company is registered as a private limited company in the UK and maintains an active status.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/31bee752-c39c-42bf-9719-ce621b491fca.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-16T00:00:00+00:00', '31bee752-c39c-42bf-9719-ce621b491fca') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Farsound', 'Farsound Aviation Limited', 'https://farsound.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/farsound-aviation-limited', 'Farsound Aviation Limited is a global supply chain and logistics solutions provider based in Brentwood, England. Founded in 1979, the company specializes in the distribution of aircraft engine parts for the aerospace industry. Farsound serves a variety of sectors, including aviation, aerospace, defense, marine, and petrochemical, focusing on delivering factory-new, fully traceable parts directly to production lines worldwide.

The company offers a range of tailored supply chain solutions, such as procurement consolidation, kitting solutions, and vendor managed inventory. Farsound emphasizes reliable on-time delivery and competitive pricing, supported by 24-hour customer service and a real-time web dashboard for order tracking. With a commitment to quality control and global expansion, Farsound maintains a vast inventory of aircraft engine parts to meet the needs of its clients efficiently.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/08d6d44a-9d26-49d1-a9c4-15d9ce565056.png', TRUE, 'Medium-sized company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-02-25T00:00:00+00:00', '08d6d44a-9d26-49d1-a9c4-15d9ce565056') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Feed Me Light', 'Feed Me Light Limited', 'https://feedmelight.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/feedmelight', 'Feed Me Light Ltd. is an independent animation studio and production company located in London, United Kingdom. The studio specializes in high-end 2D and 3D animation for a variety of projects, including commercials, games, TV series, social media content, music videos, NFTs, stop motion, short films, and charity initiatives. With a team of approximately 15 employees, the company emphasizes creativity, humor, and attention to detail in its work.

Founded with a commitment to quality and collaboration, Feed Me Light promotes open communication with clients and employees. The company also engages in corporate social responsibility by donating a portion of its proceeds to a selected charity each year. Their services range from strategic consultancy to execution, covering creative briefs, storyboarding, illustrations, filming, post-production, and more, ensuring tailored content for diverse entertainment and advertising needs.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b7277f16-b7c9-4181-983e-6fe9d22fa691.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-03-04T00:00:00+00:00', 'b7277f16-b7c9-4181-983e-6fe9d22fa691') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Flowdesk', 'Flowdesk UK Ltd', 'https://flowdesk.co', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/flowdesk-france', 'Flowdesk is a financial technology company founded in 2020 that specializes in cryptocurrency and digital asset services. The company offers a range of solutions, including market-making, liquidity provision, OTC trading, brokerage, custody, and treasury management. Flowdesk focuses on creating transparent and regulated trading infrastructure for token issuers, exchanges, institutions, and web3 players.

Headquartered in multiple global locations, including Paris and Singapore, Flowdesk provides 24/7 market access and support. The company has developed scalable trading platforms that utilize proprietary execution algorithms and risk management tools, connecting to over 140 centralized and decentralized exchanges. Flowdesk emphasizes compliance as a registered Digital Asset Service Provider with France''s Financial Markets Authority. It has successfully raised significant funding, including a Series B round of $50 million in January 2024.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ac719433-e04d-45a0-ba64-22f180f30f6f.png', TRUE, 'Medium-sized company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-03-05T00:00:00+00:00', 'ac719433-e04d-45a0-ba64-22f180f30f6f') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Forestreet', 'FORESTREET LTD', 'https://www.forestreet.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/forestreet', 'Forestreet is a UK-based software development and consulting company founded in 2017. It offers an AI-powered SaaS platform designed for vendor and market discovery, enabling procurement professionals to efficiently map suppliers and analyze markets. The platform provides unbiased insights across various geographies and categories, helping businesses quickly become category experts.

Headquartered in London, Forestreet operates in business and domestic software development and management consultancy. The company emphasizes a mission to democratize the global research industry by delivering data-driven insights. Its platform features capabilities such as on-demand supplier mapping, instant searches, market categorization, and high-quality analytics. These tools support procurement teams in enhancing their sourcing strategies and adapting to supply chain challenges. Forestreet''s analytics are utilized by major consultancies, corporates, and private equity funds for market analysis and vendor scouting.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/eb163f5b-b797-4114-bbe6-bbbad2453fcc.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-12T00:00:00+00:00', 'eb163f5b-b797-4114-bbe6-bbbad2453fcc') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Fortesium', 'Fortesium Ltd', 'https://fortesium.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fortesium', 'Fortesium Limited is a UK-based software company that specializes in cloud-based Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) solutions for regulatory bodies and professional associations. Established in 2010, the company is headquartered in Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex. Fortesium is recognized as the only UK provider of commercial off-the-shelf (COTS) solutions specifically designed for regulators, focusing on secure and efficient member management throughout the regulatory lifecycle.

The company offers three customizable SaaS platforms: Regulator Online, Regulator Smart, and Association Smart. Regulator Online streamlines registrant lifecycle processes, automating workflows to support paperless operations. Regulator Smart serves as a mid-tier solution for regulatory management, while Association Smart is tailored for membership management in professional associations. Fortesium''s solutions have led to significant cost savings and efficiency improvements for clients, including substantial reductions in printing and postage expenses.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4ce12d13-e26c-4ca8-ae04-6ca9ad0f99ad.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-09T00:00:00+00:00', '4ce12d13-e26c-4ca8-ae04-6ca9ad0f99ad') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('GBE Group', 'GBE Services London Limited', 'https://gbeservices.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gbegroup', 'GBE Group is a mechanically-biased Building Services Contractor based in London, specializing in modular and pre-fabricated construction solutions. Established in 2002, the company has developed a strong reputation for delivering complex construction projects in the region. With a workforce of approximately 118 employees, GBE focuses on innovative approaches to building services.

The company offers a range of services, including in-house design and engineering, offsite manufacture, and mechanical, electrical, and public health installation. GBE operates one of the largest off-site fabrication facilities in Southeast England, allowing for the efficient production of prefabricated components. Their notable projects include the full fit-out of 308 high-end apartments at the Battersea Power Station redevelopment.

GBE Group emphasizes an engineering-led approach to project delivery, prioritizing internal capabilities and promoting diversity within its workforce. The company is committed to maintaining high standards in all aspects of its operations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/bdcaa09b-257d-4403-8416-35cd7c72acec.png', TRUE, 'Medium-sized company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-16T00:00:00+00:00', 'bdcaa09b-257d-4403-8416-35cd7c72acec') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('GPE', 'Great Portland Estate PLC', 'https://www.gpe.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gpelondon', 'Great Portland Estates PLC (GPE) is a property investment and development company focused on Central London real estate. With a portfolio valued at approximately £2.4-2.6 billion, GPE owns around 2.7 million square feet of predominantly commercial properties, including 70% offices, 28% retail, and 2% residential. The company was incorporated in 1957 and became publicly quoted in 1959. It transitioned to a Real Estate Investment Trust in 2006 and emphasizes an entrepreneurial culture and strong stakeholder relationships.

GPE''s core activities include developing building projects and buying and selling real estate. The company aims to unlock potential in undervalued properties by repositioning them for diverse occupiers. Sustainability is a key focus, with initiatives targeting energy reductions and waste diversion. GPE offers customizable office spaces, fully managed offices, and prime retail locations in areas like Fitzrovia, Soho, and Mayfair, all designed to meet the evolving needs of London''s market.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/086292d2-c0b3-46e8-9263-25b5cac90ab3.png', TRUE, 'Medium-sized company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-02-23T00:00:00+00:00', '086292d2-c0b3-46e8-9263-25b5cac90ab3') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('GreenEnco', 'GREENENCO LIMITED', 'https://greenenco.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/greenenco-limited', 'GreenEnco Limited is a UK-based renewable energy advisory firm founded in 2017. The company specializes in technical advisory, engineering solutions, and risk management for solar PV, battery energy storage systems (BESS), and solar EV projects. GreenEnco supports projects throughout their lifecycle, from concept to operations, and has delivered services to over 15 GW of projects in 16 countries.

The firm offers a range of services, including techno-commercial due diligence, risk management, and operational asset optimization. One of its key offerings is Asset Performance Management (APM), which utilizes AI and machine learning to enhance energy efficiency and generation for solar assets. GreenEnco''s mission is to safeguard asset life with integrity, and it aims to provide solutions for a seamless transition to net-zero energy. With a team that has over 50 years of cumulative experience, GreenEnco is recognized as a high-potential UK SME in smart energy innovations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/05a2d7b4-d825-45f9-8bf8-a2f1f3926bdf.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-17T00:00:00+00:00', '05a2d7b4-d825-45f9-8bf8-a2f1f3926bdf') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Harver', 'Launchpad Recruits Ltd', 'https://harver.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/harver', 'Harver is an AI-powered pre-employment assessment and talent acquisition platform founded in 2015, with roots dating back to 2013. Headquartered in New York, NY, and with additional offices in Dallas, TX, and Amsterdam, Harver operates in the human resources software industry. The company employs between 201 and 500 staff and has processed over 100 million candidates, serving more than 1,300 customers globally.

Harver offers a suite of automated, predictive hiring solutions designed to enhance the recruitment process. Their services include predictive assessments that align candidates with job profiles, hiring automation tools for managing high-volume applications, and dashboards that provide real-time data visualization and insights. The platform focuses on improving candidate engagement and reducing bias, making it suitable for organizations of all sizes. Notable clients include Netflix, Uber, Booking.com, and Peloton.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 1, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ad950378-d7d8-4259-8047-79f55199517d.png', TRUE, 'Medium-sized company', NULL, NULL, FALSE, '2026-02-23T00:00:00+00:00', 'ad950378-d7d8-4259-8047-79f55199517d') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('Hydroluminum', 'HYDROLUMINUM LIMITED', 'https://www.hydroluminum.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hydroluminum', 'At Hydroluminum, we revolutionise sustainable energy and resource recovery. Our proprietary technology transforms waste aluminium into green hydrogen, aluminium hydroxide, and fossil‐free steam—all through a zero-emission process. Designed to be compact and modular, our system offers decentralised energy solutions for industrial decarbonisation, transport, and grid storage, while supporting a circular economy. Join us as we drive the transition to a cleaner, more sustainable future.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0acb2ca7-62d1-48d4-b819-4b5998e0e037.png', TRUE, 'Small company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-13T00:00:00+00:00', '0acb2ca7-62d1-48d4-b819-4b5998e0e037') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO companies (trading_name, companies_house_name, url, url_linkedin, description, policy, open_to_sponsorship, active_jobs_count, url_favicon, licensed_sponsor, estimated_num_employees_label, cos_used_count_2025, sponsored_employees_count, show_recently_added_badge, added_to_register, favicon_id) VALUES ('INTEC Energy Solutions', 'INTEC ENERGY SOLUTIONS LIMITED', 'https://in-tecenergy.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/intec-energy-solutions', 'INTEC Energy Solutions is a global provider of engineering, procurement, and construction (EPC) services, specializing in renewable energy. The company focuses on turnkey solar power plants and battery energy storage systems (BESS), emphasizing sustainability and efficiency. Headquartered in the United Kingdom, INTEC has a presence in multiple countries, including Germany, Türkiye, Australia, New Zealand, Azerbaijan, Romania, and Mauritius.

INTEC offers a range of services, including project management, design, and installation for utility-scale projects, as well as consultancy in energy engineering and operations and maintenance for long-term system performance. The company has completed over 180 projects worldwide, achieving a significant installed capacity and is committed to pioneering new energy solutions to support the global energy transition. With a dedicated workforce and a focus on high-quality, eco-friendly power generation, INTEC serves international investors and project developers in the renewable energy sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', 4, 0, 'https://xhtezeeaeqjfdhrkltox.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d8de6c88-37c7-4181-8ac8-bc06cae4771d.png', TRUE, 'Large company', NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2026-03-09T00:00:00+00:00', 'd8de6c88-37c7-4181-8ac8-bc06cae4771d') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
